				\begin{document}$$\bar{v}$$\end{document}v¯, i.e., the theoretical average daily distance traveled by individuals. This is a measure that is not readily estimable, which is why in the present work we showed results for a series of credible scenarios; however, using mobility data from European cities we managed to obtain credible figures to plug-in the model. Our model does take into account interpersonal distance in the form of R parameter; a potential expansion of this framework is to account for time spent within the 1 m interpersonal distance, as well as distinguishing between high-risk (e.g., taxis, buses) and low-risk (e.g., walking, personal car) means of transportation.

